@graph.rdfs:comment: A [callsign](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Call_sign), as used in broadcasting and radio communications to identify people, radio and TV stations, or vehicles.
@graph.rdfs:label: callSign

@graph.rdfs:comment:
The time needed to accelerate the vehicle from a given start velocity to a given target velocity.

Typical unit code(s): SEC for seconds

* Note: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for seconds/0..100 km/h or seconds/0..60 mph. Simply use "SEC" for seconds and indicate the velocities in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]], or use [[valueReference]] with a [[QuantitativeValue]] of 0..60 mph or 0..100 km/h to specify the reference speeds.
@graph.rdfs:label: accelerationTime

@graph.rdfs:comment: PaidLeave: this is a benefit for paid leave.
@graph.rdfs:label: PaidLeave

@graph.rdfs:comment: The date on which the CreativeWork was created or the item was added to a DataFeed.
@graph.rdfs:label: dateCreated

@graph.rdfs:comment: A single message from a sender to one or more organizations or people.
@graph.rdfs:label: Message

@graph.rdfs:comment: A diet conforming to Hindu dietary practices, in particular, beef-free.
@graph.rdfs:label: HinduDiet

@graph.rdfs:comment: The quantity that results by performing instructions. For example, a paper airplane, 10 personalized candles.
@graph.rdfs:label: yield

@graph.rdfs:comment: The status for a previously confirmed reservation that is now cancelled.
@graph.rdfs:label: ReservationCancelled

@graph.rdfs:comment: Only consensus opinion of experts, case studies, or standard-of-care.
@graph.rdfs:label: EvidenceLevelC

@graph.rdfs:comment: A single feed providing structured information about one or more entities or topics.
@graph.rdfs:label: DataFeed

@graph.rdfs:comment: This Review or Rating is relevant to this part or facet of the itemReviewed.
@graph.rdfs:label: reviewAspect

@graph.rdfs:comment: Event type: Festival.
@graph.rdfs:label: Festival

@graph.rdfs:comment: This incentive is currently active.
@graph.rdfs:label: IncentiveStatusActive

@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of consuming written content.
@graph.rdfs:label: ReadAction

@graph.rdfs:comment: Certification information about a product, organization, service, place, or person.
@graph.rdfs:label: hasCertification

@graph.rdfs:comment: Any matter of defined composition that has discrete existence, whose origin may be biological, mineral or chemical.
@graph.rdfs:label: Substance

@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of participating in performance arts.
@graph.rdfs:label: PerformAction

@graph.rdfs:comment: A graveyard.
@graph.rdfs:label: Cemetery

@graph.rdfs:comment: A characteristic of the described resource that is physiologically dangerous to some users. Related to WCAG 2.0 guideline 2.3. Values should be drawn from the [approved vocabulary](https://www.w3.org/2021/a11y-discov-vocab/latest/#accessibilityHazard-vocabulary).
@graph.rdfs:label: accessibilityHazard

@graph.rdfs:comment: Maximum girth of bust. Used, for example, to fit women's suits.
@graph.rdfs:label: BodyMeasurementBust

@graph.rdfs:comment: Any condition of the human body that affects the normal functioning of a person, whether physically or mentally. Includes diseases, injuries, disabilities, disorders, syndromes, etc.
@graph.rdfs:label: MedicalCondition

@graph.rdfs:comment: A text file. The text can be unformatted or contain markup, html, etc.
@graph.rdfs:label: TextObject

@graph.rdfs:comment: A page devoted to a single item, such as a particular product or hotel.
@graph.rdfs:label: ItemPage

@graph.rdfs:comment: A specific branch of medical science that pertains to the health care of women, particularly in the diagnosis and treatment of disorders affecting the female reproductive system.
@graph.rdfs:label: Gynecologic

@graph.rdfs:comment: Networks covered by this plan.
@graph.rdfs:label: includesHealthPlanNetwork

@graph.rdfs:comment: A release of this album.
@graph.rdfs:label: albumRelease

@graph.rdfs:comment: Device used to perform the test.
@graph.rdfs:label: usesDevice

@graph.rdfs:comment: The album this is a release of.
@graph.rdfs:label: releaseOf

@graph.rdfs:comment: The specific biochemical interaction through which this drug or supplement produces its pharmacological effect.
@graph.rdfs:label: mechanismOfAction

@graph.rdfs:comment: The status of payment; whether the invoice has been paid or not.
@graph.rdfs:label: paymentStatus

@graph.rdfs:comment: A type of boarding policy used by an airline.
@graph.rdfs:label: BoardingPolicyType

@graph.rdfs:comment: The number of axles.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62.
@graph.rdfs:label: numberOfAxles

@graph.rdfs:comment: How the procedure is performed.
@graph.rdfs:label: howPerformed

@graph.rdfs:comment: A sub property of instrument. The method of delivery.
@graph.rdfs:label: deliveryMethod

@graph.rdfs:comment: An organization that provides flights for passengers.
@graph.rdfs:label: Airline

@graph.rdfs:comment: Design models for medical trials. Enumerated type.
@graph.rdfs:label: MedicalTrialDesign

@graph.rdfs:comment: The branches that delineate from the nerve bundle. Not to be confused with [[branchOf]].
@graph.rdfs:label: branch

@graph.rdfs:comment: The identifier of the transaction.
@graph.rdfs:label: orderNumber

@graph.rdfs:comment: A moving company.
@graph.rdfs:label: MovingCompany

@graph.rdfs:comment: UnemploymentSupport: this is a benefit for unemployment support.
@graph.rdfs:label: UnemploymentSupport

@graph.rdfs:comment: An apartment (in American English) or flat (in British English) is a self-contained housing unit (a type of residential real estate) that occupies only part of a building (source: Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Apartment).
@graph.rdfs:label: Apartment

@graph.rdfs:comment: Intended audience for an item, i.e. the group for whom the item was created.
@graph.rdfs:label: Audience

@graph.rdfs:comment: Payment in advance by bank transfer, equivalent to http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#ByBankTransferInAdvance.
@graph.rdfs:label: ByBankTransferInAdvance

@graph.rdfs:comment: The cost per unit of a medical drug. Note that this type is not meant to represent the price in an offer of a drug for sale; see the Offer type for that. This type will typically be used to tag wholesale or average retail cost of a drug, or maximum reimbursable cost. Costs of medical drugs vary widely depending on how and where they are paid for, so while this type captures some of the variables, costs should be used with caution by consumers of this schema's markup.
@graph.rdfs:label: DrugCost

@graph.rdfs:comment: The publisher of the article in question.
@graph.rdfs:label: publisher

@graph.rdfs:comment: The current status of the order.
@graph.rdfs:label: orderStatus

@graph.rdfs:comment: Specifies the least energy efficient class on the regulated EU energy consumption scale for the product category a product belongs to. For example, energy consumption for televisions placed on the market after January 1, 2020 is scaled from D to A+++.
@graph.rdfs:label: energyEfficiencyScaleMin

@graph.rdfs:comment: The earliest someone may check into a lodging establishment.
@graph.rdfs:label: checkinTime

@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of capturing sound and moving images on film, video, or digitally.
@graph.rdfs:label: FilmAction

@graph.rdfs:comment: The actual body of the article.
@graph.rdfs:label: articleBody

@graph.rdfs:comment: Information about the engine of the vehicle. A vehicle can have multiple engines represented by multiple engine specification entities.
@graph.rdfs:label: EngineSpecification

@graph.rdfs:comment: A [[CategoryCodeSet]] that contains this category code.
@graph.rdfs:label: inCodeSet

@graph.rdfs:comment: Specific physiologic risks associated to the diet plan.
@graph.rdfs:label: risks

@graph.rdfs:comment: The individual who traces over the pencil drawings in ink after pencils are complete.
@graph.rdfs:label: inker

@graph.rdfs:comment: Non-proprietary identifier for molecular entity that can be used in printed and electronic data sources thus enabling easier linking of diverse data compilations.
@graph.rdfs:label: inChI

@graph.rdfs:comment: Categorization and other types related to a topic.
@graph.rdfs:label: TypesHealthAspect

@graph.rdfs:comment: An incentive that reduces/exempts the recipient from taxation applicable to the incentivized good/service (e.g. luxury taxes, registration taxes, circulation tax).
@graph.rdfs:label: IncentiveTypeTaxWaiver

@graph.rdfs:comment: A citation or reference to another creative work, such as another publication, web page, scholarly article, etc.
@graph.rdfs:label: citation

@graph.rdfs:comment: The item is intended to induce bodily harm, for example guns, mace, combat knives, brass knuckles, nail or other bombs, and spears.
@graph.rdfs:label: WeaponConsideration

@graph.rdfs:comment: Provides additional qualification to an observation. For example, a GDP observation measures the Nominal value.
@graph.rdfs:label: measurementQualifier

@graph.rdfs:comment:
The act of playing/exercising/training/performing for enjoyment, leisure, recreation, competition or exercise.

Related actions:

* [[ListenAction]]: Unlike ListenAction (which is under ConsumeAction), PlayAction refers to performing for an audience or at an event, rather than consuming music.
* [[WatchAction]]: Unlike WatchAction (which is under ConsumeAction), PlayAction refers to showing/displaying for an audience or at an event, rather than consuming visual content.
@graph.rdfs:label: PlayAction

@graph.rdfs:comment: Indicates that the item has limited availability.
@graph.rdfs:label: LimitedAvailability

@graph.rdfs:comment: Aquarium.
@graph.rdfs:label: Aquarium

@graph.rdfs:comment: Specifies that the consumer can keep the product, even when receiving a refund or store credit.
@graph.rdfs:label: KeepProduct

@graph.rdfs:comment: Natural languages such as Spanish, Tamil, Hindi, English, etc. Formal language code tags expressed in [BCP 47](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IETF_language_tag) can be used via the [[alternateName]] property. The Language type previously also covered programming languages such as Scheme and Lisp, which are now best represented using [[ComputerLanguage]].
@graph.rdfs:label: Language

@graph.rdfs:comment: Genre of the creative work, broadcast channel or group.
@graph.rdfs:label: genre

@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of consuming static visual content.
@graph.rdfs:label: ViewAction

@graph.rdfs:comment: Nutritional information about the recipe.
@graph.rdfs:label: NutritionInformation

@graph.rdfs:comment: A reservation for an event like a concert, sporting event, or lecture.\n\nNote: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, use [[Offer]].
@graph.rdfs:label: EventReservation

@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of producing a balanced opinion about the object for an audience. An agent reviews an object with participants resulting in a review.
@graph.rdfs:label: ReviewAction

@graph.rdfs:comment: HealthCare: this is a benefit for health care.
@graph.rdfs:label: HealthCare

@graph.rdfs:comment: The vasculature the lymphatic structure runs, or efferents, to.
@graph.rdfs:label: runsTo

@graph.rdfs:comment: The geographic shape of a place. A GeoShape can be described using several properties whose values are based on latitude/longitude pairs. Either whitespace or commas can be used to separate latitude and longitude; whitespace should be used when writing a list of several such points.
@graph.rdfs:label: GeoShape

@graph.rdfs:comment:
The volume swept by all of the pistons inside the cylinders of an internal combustion engine in a single movement. 

Typical unit code(s): CMQ for cubic centimeter, LTR for liters, INQ for cubic inches
* Note 1: You can link to information about how the given value has been determined using the [[valueReference]] property.
* Note 2: You can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.
@graph.rdfs:label: engineDisplacement

@graph.rdfs:comment: UserInteraction and its subtypes is an old way of talking about users interacting with pages. It is generally better to use [[Action]]-based vocabulary, alongside types such as [[Comment]].
@graph.rdfs:label: UserLikes

@graph.rdfs:comment: A theater or other performing art center.
@graph.rdfs:label: PerformingArtsTheater

@graph.rdfs:comment: A link to the ListItem that precedes the current one.
@graph.rdfs:label: previousItem

@graph.rdfs:comment: Nonprofit501c7: Non-profit type referring to Social and Recreational Clubs.
@graph.rdfs:label: Nonprofit501c7

@graph.rdfs:comment: A maintainer of a [[Dataset]], software package ([[SoftwareApplication]]), or other [[Project]]. A maintainer is a [[Person]] or [[Organization]] that manages contributions to, and/or publication of, some (typically complex) artifact. It is common for distributions of software and data to be based on "upstream" sources. When [[maintainer]] is applied to a specific version of something e.g. a particular version or packaging of a [[Dataset]], it is always  possible that the upstream source has a different maintainer. The [[isBasedOn]] property can be used to indicate such relationships between datasets to make the different maintenance roles clear. Similarly in the case of software, a package may have dedicated maintainers working on integration into software distributions such as Ubuntu, as well as upstream maintainers of the underlying work.
@graph.rdfs:label: maintainer

@graph.rdfs:comment: The brand(s) associated with a product or service, or the brand(s) maintained by an organization or business person.
@graph.rdfs:label: brand

@graph.rdfs:comment: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a containing geometry to a contained geometry. "a contains b iff no points of b lie in the exterior of a, and at least one point of the interior of b lies in the interior of a". As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).
@graph.rdfs:label: geoContains

@graph.rdfs:comment: Medical clinicians, including practicing physicians and other medical professionals involved in clinical practice.
@graph.rdfs:label: Clinician

@graph.rdfs:comment: Of a [[Person]], and less typically of an [[Organization]], to indicate a known language. We do not distinguish skill levels or reading/writing/speaking/signing here. Use language codes from the [IETF BCP 47 standard](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47).
@graph.rdfs:label: knowsLanguage

@graph.rdfs:comment: The vasculature that the vein drains into.
@graph.rdfs:label: drainsTo

@graph.rdfs:comment: One of a set of differential diagnoses for the condition. Specifically, a closely-related or competing diagnosis typically considered later in the cognitive process whereby this medical condition is distinguished from others most likely responsible for a similar collection of signs and symptoms to reach the most parsimonious diagnosis or diagnoses in a patient.
@graph.rdfs:label: differentialDiagnosis

@graph.rdfs:comment:
Provides positive considerations regarding something, for example product highlights or (alongside [[negativeNotes]]) pro/con lists for reviews.

In the case of a [[Review]], the property describes the [[itemReviewed]] from the perspective of the review; in the case of a [[Product]], the product itself is being described.

The property values can be expressed either as unstructured text (repeated as necessary), or if ordered, as a list (in which case the most positive is at the beginning of the list).
@graph.rdfs:label: positiveNotes

@graph.rdfs:comment: The status of a medical study. Enumerated type.
@graph.rdfs:label: MedicalStudyStatus

@graph.rdfs:comment: A specific object or file containing a Legislation. Note that the same Legislation can be published in multiple files. For example, a digitally signed PDF, a plain PDF and an HTML version.
@graph.rdfs:label: LegislationObject

@graph.rdfs:comment:
A 3D model represents some kind of 3D content, which may have [[encoding]]s in one or more [[MediaObject]]s. Many 3D formats are available (e.g. see [Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Category:3D_graphics_file_formats)); specific encoding formats can be represented using the [[encodingFormat]] property applied to the relevant [[MediaObject]]. For the
case of a single file published after Zip compression, the convention of appending '+zip' to the [[encodingFormat]] can be used. Geospatial, AR/VR, artistic/animation, gaming, engineering and scientific content can all be represented using [[3DModel]].
@graph.rdfs:label: 3DModel

@graph.rdfs:comment: Payment in advance in some form of shop or kiosk for goods purchased online.
@graph.rdfs:label: InStorePrepay

@graph.rdfs:comment: Genitourinary system function assessment with clinical examination.
@graph.rdfs:label: Genitourinary

@graph.rdfs:comment: Indicates a textual identifier for a ProductGroup.
@graph.rdfs:label: productGroupID

@graph.rdfs:comment: numtotbeds - ALL HOSPITAL BEDS: Total number of all inpatient and outpatient beds, including all staffed, ICU, licensed, and overflow (surge) beds used for inpatients or outpatients.
@graph.rdfs:label: cvdNumTotBeds

@graph.rdfs:comment: Indicates an OfferCatalog listing for this Organization, Person, or Service.
@graph.rdfs:label: hasOfferCatalog

@graph.rdfs:comment:
An offer to transfer some rights to an item or to provide a service  for example, an offer to sell tickets to an event, to rent the DVD of a movie, to stream a TV show over the internet, to repair a motorcycle, or to loan a book.

Note: As the [[businessFunction]] property, which identifies the form of offer (e.g. sell, lease, repair, dispose), defaults to http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Sell; an Offer without a defined businessFunction value can be assumed to be an offer to sell.

For [GTIN](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin)-related fields, see [Check Digit calculator](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/support/check_digit_calculator) and [validation guide](http://www.gs1us.org/resources/standards/gtin-validation-guide) from [GS1](http://www.gs1.org/).
@graph.rdfs:label: Offer

@graph.rdfs:comment: A pointer to another, functionally similar product (or multiple products).
@graph.rdfs:label: isSimilarTo

@graph.rdfs:comment: Size group "Regular" for wearables.
@graph.rdfs:label: WearableSizeGroupRegular

@graph.rdfs:comment: A description of any security clearance requirements of the job.
@graph.rdfs:label: securityClearanceRequirement

@graph.rdfs:comment: The words in the song.
@graph.rdfs:label: lyrics

@graph.rdfs:comment: Any medical test, typically performed for diagnostic purposes.
@graph.rdfs:label: MedicalTest

@graph.rdfs:comment: A pattern that something has, for example 'polka dot', 'striped', 'Canadian flag'. Values are typically expressed as text, although links to controlled value schemes are also supported.
@graph.rdfs:label: pattern

@graph.rdfs:comment: Nonprofit501c20: Non-profit type referring to Group Legal Services Plan Organizations.
@graph.rdfs:label: Nonprofit501c20

@graph.rdfs:comment: A type of bed. This is used for indicating the bed or beds available in an accommodation.
@graph.rdfs:label: BedType

@graph.rdfs:comment: The TV series to which this episode or season belongs.
@graph.rdfs:label: partOfTVSeries

@graph.rdfs:comment: The release date of a vehicle model (often used to differentiate versions of the same make and model).
@graph.rdfs:label: modelDate

@graph.rdfs:comment: A pointer to another product (or multiple products) for which this product is a consumable.
@graph.rdfs:label: isConsumableFor

@graph.rdfs:comment: Content coded as 'trained algorithmic media' using the IPTC digital source type vocabulary.
@graph.rdfs:label: TrainedAlgorithmicMediaDigitalSource

@graph.rdfs:comment: Information about school closures.
@graph.rdfs:label: schoolClosuresInfo

@graph.rdfs:comment: A sub property of object. The object that replaces.
@graph.rdfs:label: replacer

@graph.rdfs:comment: Specifies browser requirements in human-readable text. For example, 'requires HTML5 support'.
@graph.rdfs:label: browserRequirements

@graph.rdfs:comment:
A motel.

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.
@graph.rdfs:label: Motel

@graph.rdfs:comment: A description of the types of physical activity associated with the job. Defined terms such as those in O*net may be used, but note that there is no way to specify the level of ability as well as its nature when using a defined term.
@graph.rdfs:label: physicalRequirement

@graph.rdfs:comment: Lung and respiratory system clinical examination.
@graph.rdfs:label: Lung

@graph.rdfs:comment: A specific branch of medical science that pertains to diagnosis and treatment of disorders of skin.
@graph.rdfs:label: Dermatology

@graph.rdfs:comment: Represents additional information about a relationship or property. For example a Role can be used to say that a 'member' role linking some SportsTeam to a player occurred during a particular time period. Or that a Person's 'actor' role in a Movie was for some particular characterName. Such properties can be attached to a Role entity, which is then associated with the main entities using ordinary properties like 'member' or 'actor'.\n\nSee also [blog post](http://blog.schema.org/2014/06/introducing-role.html).
@graph.rdfs:label: Role

@graph.rdfs:comment: The act of participating in an exchange of goods and services for monetary compensation. An agent trades an object, product or service with a participant in exchange for a one time or periodic payment.
@graph.rdfs:label: TradeAction

@graph.rdfs:comment: The typical delay between the receipt of the order and the goods either leaving the warehouse or being prepared for pickup, in case the delivery method is on site pickup.
@graph.rdfs:label: deliveryLeadTime

@graph.rdfs:comment: Indicates the design and body style of the vehicle (e.g. station wagon, hatchback, etc.).
@graph.rdfs:label: bodyType

@graph.rdfs:comment: A statistical distribution of values.
@graph.rdfs:label: QuantitativeValueDistribution

@graph.rdfs:comment: A vet's office.
@graph.rdfs:label: VeterinaryCare

@graph.rdfs:comment: Minimal age of the child.
@graph.rdfs:label: childMinAge

@graph.rdfs:comment: A unique identifier for the reservation.
@graph.rdfs:label: reservationId

@graph.rdfs:comment: Represents EU Energy Efficiency Class A as defined in EU energy labeling regulations.
@graph.rdfs:label: EUEnergyEfficiencyCategoryA

@graph.rdfs:comment: A company or fund that gathers capital from a number of investors to create a pool of money that is then re-invested into stocks, bonds and other assets.
@graph.rdfs:label: InvestmentFund

@graph.rdfs:comment: Describes a reservation for travel, dining or an event. Some reservations require tickets. \n\nNote: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, restaurant reservations, flights, or rental cars, use [[Offer]].
@graph.rdfs:label: Reservation

@graph.rdfs:comment: Cardiovascular system assessment with clinical examination.
@graph.rdfs:label: CardiovascularExam

@graph.rdfs:comment: A measurement of an item, For example, the inseam of pants, the wheel size of a bicycle, the gauge of a screw, or the carbon footprint measured for certification by an authority. Usually an exact measurement, but can also be a range of measurements for adjustable products, for example belts and ski bindings.
@graph.rdfs:label: hasMeasurement

@graph.rdfs:comment: The color or color combination of the interior of the vehicle.
@graph.rdfs:label: vehicleInteriorColor

@graph.rdfs:comment: A part of a successively published publication such as a periodical or multi-volume work, often numbered. It may represent a time span, such as a year.\n\nSee also [blog post](https://blog-schema.org/2014/09/02/schema-org-support-for-bibliographic-relationships-and-periodicals/).
@graph.rdfs:label: PublicationVolume

@graph.rdfs:comment:
The "temporal" property can be used in cases where more specific properties
(e.g. [[temporalCoverage]], [[dateCreated]], [[dateModified]], [[datePublished]]) are not known to be appropriate.
@graph.rdfs:label: temporal

@graph.rdfs:comment: A movie.
@graph.rdfs:label: Movie

@graph.rdfs:comment: The date after when the item is not valid. For example the end of an offer, salary period, or a period of opening hours.
@graph.rdfs:label: validThrough

@graph.rdfs:comment: Rigid connective tissue that comprises up the skeletal structure of the human body.
@graph.rdfs:label: Bone

@graph.rdfs:comment: Neck assessment with clinical examination.
@graph.rdfs:label: Neck

@graph.rdfs:comment: A medical test typically performed given this condition.
@graph.rdfs:label: typicalTest

@graph.rdfs:comment: A position played, performed or filled by a person or organization, as part of an organization. For example, an athlete in a SportsTeam might play in the position named 'Quarterback'.
@graph.rdfs:label: namedPosition

@graph.rdfs:comment: The Order(s) related to this Invoice. One or more Orders may be combined into a single Invoice.
@graph.rdfs:label: referencesOrder

@graph.rdfs:comment: The type of the medical article, taken from the US NLM MeSH publication type catalog. See also [MeSH documentation](http://www.nlm.nih.gov/mesh/pubtypes.html).
@graph.rdfs:label: publicationType

@graph.rdfs:comment: Comments, typically from users.
@graph.rdfs:label: comment

@graph.rdfs:comment: A comment on an item - for example, a comment on a blog post. The comment's content is expressed via the [[text]] property, and its topic via [[about]], properties shared with all CreativeWorks.
@graph.rdfs:label: Comment

@graph.rdfs:comment: Represents EU Energy Efficiency Class A+++ as defined in EU energy labeling regulations.
@graph.rdfs:label: EUEnergyEfficiencyCategoryA3Plus

@graph.rdfs:comment: The number of comments this CreativeWork (e.g. Article, Question or Answer) has received. This is most applicable to works published in Web sites with commenting system; additional comments may exist elsewhere.
@graph.rdfs:label: commentCount

@graph.rdfs:comment: GS1 (formerly NRF) size system for wearables.
@graph.rdfs:label: WearableSizeSystemGS1

@graph.rdfs:comment: The conventional Western system of medicine, that aims to apply the best available evidence gained from the scientific method to clinical decision making. Also known as conventional or Western medicine.
@graph.rdfs:label: WesternConventional

@graph.rdfs:comment: An honorific prefix preceding a Person's name such as Dr/Mrs/Mr.
@graph.rdfs:label: honorificPrefix

@graph.rdfs:comment: e.g. Painting, Drawing, Sculpture, Print, Photograph, Assemblage, Collage, etc.
@graph.rdfs:label: artform

@graph.rdfs:comment: Enumerates common size groups for various product categories.
@graph.rdfs:label: SizeGroupEnumeration

@graph.rdfs:comment: The place where the person died.
@graph.rdfs:label: deathPlace

@graph.rdfs:comment: Size group "Extra Short" for wearables.
@graph.rdfs:label: WearableSizeGroupExtraShort

@graph.rdfs:comment: United Kingdom size system for wearables.
@graph.rdfs:label: WearableSizeSystemUK

@graph.rdfs:comment: Whether borrower is a resident of the jurisdiction where the property is located.
@graph.rdfs:label: domiciledMortgage

@graph.rdfs:comment: ICAO identifier for an airport.
@graph.rdfs:label: icaoCode

@graph.rdfs:comment: Amount of shipping costs for product returns (for any reason). Applicable when property [[returnFees]] equals [[ReturnShippingFees]].
@graph.rdfs:label: returnShippingFeesAmount

@graph.rdfs:comment: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) are topologically equal, as defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM). "Two geometries are topologically equal if their interiors intersect and no part of the interior or boundary of one geometry intersects the exterior of the other" (a symmetric relationship).
@graph.rdfs:label: geoEquals

@graph.rdfs:comment: A diet exclusive of all animal products.
@graph.rdfs:label: VeganDiet

@graph.rdfs:comment: An item within a data feed. Data feeds may have many elements.
@graph.rdfs:label: dataFeedElement

@graph.rdfs:comment: The type of the legislation. Examples of values are "law", "act", "directive", "decree", "regulation", "statutory instrument", "loi organique", "rglement grand-ducal", etc., depending on the country.
@graph.rdfs:label: legislationType

@graph.rdfs:comment: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) are topologically disjoint: "they have no point in common. They form a set of disconnected geometries." (A symmetric relationship, as defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).)
@graph.rdfs:label: geoDisjoint

@graph.rdfs:comment: A bookstore.
@graph.rdfs:label: BookStore

@graph.rdfs:comment: MixedEventAttendanceMode - an event that is conducted as a combination of both offline and online modes.
@graph.rdfs:label: MixedEventAttendanceMode

@graph.rdfs:comment: The day of the week between Friday and Sunday.
@graph.rdfs:label: Saturday

@graph.rdfs:comment: Server that provides game interaction in a multiplayer game.

@graph.rdfs:comment:
The speed range of the vehicle. If the vehicle is powered by an engine, the upper limit of the speed range (indicated by [[maxValue]]) should be the maximum speed achievable under regular conditions.

Typical unit code(s): KMH for km/h, HM for mile per hour (0.447 04 m/s), KNT for knot

*Note 1: Use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate the range. Typically, the minimal value is zero.
* Note 2: There are many different ways of measuring the speed range. You can link to information about how the given value has been determined using the [[valueReference]] property.
@graph.rdfs:label: speed

@graph.rdfs:label: sizeGroup

@graph.rdfs:comment: An observational study is a type of medical study that attempts to infer the possible effect of a treatment through observation of a cohort of subjects over a period of time. In an observational study, the assignment of subjects into treatment groups versus control groups is outside the control of the investigator. This is in contrast with controlled studies, such as the randomized controlled trials represented by MedicalTrial, where each subject is randomly assigned to a treatment group or a control group before the start of the treatment.
@graph.rdfs:label: MedicalObservationalStudy

@graph.rdfs:comment:
An agent joins an event/group with participants/friends at a location.

Related actions:

* [[RegisterAction]]: Unlike RegisterAction, JoinAction refers to joining a group/team of people.
* [[SubscribeAction]]: Unlike SubscribeAction, JoinAction does not imply that you'll be receiving updates.
